# Tech Stack

The project uses the following technologies:

- **Yarn** - Package manager of choice
- **typescript** (TypeScript) - Primary language
- **next** (Next.js) - Framework (App Router, without 'src' directory)
- **payload** (PayloadCMS) - Our backend framework.
- **@payloadcms/db-postgres** (PostgreSQL) - As our database.
- **tailwindcss** (Tailwind CSS v4) - For styling
- **shadcn/ui** (Shadcn) - For general components (only if not too custom/complicated)
- **zod** (ZOD) - Data validation
- **react-email** (React Email) - For designing emails
- **resend** (Resend) - API for sending emails
- **swiper** (SwiperJS) - For creating sliders
- **lucide-react** (Lucide) - For React icons (if custom icons are not available)
- **motion** (Framer Motion) - For animations

## Custom Utility Functions

The project includes these frequently used utility functions:

### `cn()` - Class Name Utility

```typescript
export function cn(...inputs: ClassValue[]) {
  return twMerge(clsx(inputs))
}
```

Purpose: Merge Tailwind classes with conflict resolution.

### `slugify()` - Text to Slug Converter

```typescript
export function slugify(text: string) {
  return text.toLowerCase().replace(/ /g, '-').replace(/&/g, 'and')
}
```

Purpose: Convert text strings to URL-friendly slugs.

## Project Folder Structure

The project follows this directory structure:

```
/app
  /api          # NextJS API routes

/components
  /atoms        # Basic components (e.g., buttons, headings, icons)
  /molecules    # Composite components (e.g., accordions, modals, cards)
  /globals      # Global components (e.g., header, footer)
  /sections     # Page building blocks (e.g., hero-section, text-image-section, team-section)

/emails         # React-email designs

/lib
  /data         # .ts files for JSON data (when no database is used)
                # Examples: cases.ts, services.ts
  utils.ts      # Helper functions (e.g., cn() utility function, slugify() utility function)
  types.ts      # TypeScript type definitions for data
```

## NextJS Page Requirements

All NextJS pages/components MUST follow these requirements:

1. **Use React Functional Components** - No class components
2. **Declare Props Interface** - Always define an interface for component props
3. **Destructure Props** - Always destructure props in the function signature to access them directly

```typescript
export function Page(props: PropsInterface) {
  const {text, slides, darkMode} = props;
  return ()
}
```

## Code Style Guidelines

- Use TypeScript for all components
- Use Tailwind CSS classes for styling (avoid inline styles or separate CSS files when possible)
- Follow the atomic design pattern (atoms → molecules → sections)
- Export utility functions from `/lib/utils.ts`
- Define TypeScript types in `/lib/types.ts`
